</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uliquidated.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liquidated</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/15/02 7:55:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3630.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hi</span><hr size=1> I'm Liq, I'm a mod over at concerthall and know a bit about bards..... bear with me and I'll explain how amp works. If details bore you, please skip this post as I'll just bore you.<br>
<br>
bard songs fall into one of 3 classes<br>
instrument based (i.e. NEED an instrument (drum) to play level 55 occolusion of sound debuff)<br>
singing based (i.e. the 32 mana song can only be sung)<br>
hybrid singing/instrument songs that can usually benefit from the proper instrument (i.e. our heal song at level 6)<br>
<br>
before epics came out, Bards had a mod based on instruments....<br>
string<br>
wind<br>
percussion<br>
brass<br>
<br>
The way the mod work in Bardanees is that singing is 1.0 mod.... if the heal song heals 13 at 60, 1.0 times 13 = 13.... the base value for heal at 60.<br>
<br>
any and all mods that are tacked onto it are +.x but for short hand, the base 1.0 is added to any instrument mod.<br>
<br>
The normal hand drum from a store is a +1.0 mod.... short hand being 2.0... (1.0 + 1.0) <br>
<br>
One song drums are famous for is bard speed, selo's. At level 50+, the base movement mod for a bard is +65%,  or 1.65 in spdateese, that's 1.65 times 1.0 . sow is +55% (1.55), soe is +60% (1.60) and soc is +115% (2.15) max values.<br>
<br>
now a bard with a store bought drum is +65% times 2.0 meaning 2.30 total move mod.... sorry any druids/shammys that thought soc was faster than bard speed at even the most basic level.<br>
<br>
Magic instruments fall generally within the range of 1.8 to 2.5<br>
<br>
When the bard epic first came out it was total left wield bait. The ratio of 16 26 was inferior to even 10/18 in main hand so verant pruced it up by making it the holy grail of bard toys...<br>
<br>
All instrument mods and singing when used only in primary incuding singing (!!!!)... for a 1.8 mod - less that most store boughts.<br>
<br>
Not only did epic now act like all the instruments for songs that needed instruments, increasing most instrument/hybrid songs, it also boosted most singing based songs too with a few exceptions. A major boost for flagging bard abilities.<br>
<br>
This improvement was a two edged sword though (pun intended). Where the sword in primary now acted like a 1.8 mod for all instruments, it meant that we were stuck with a kunark era weapon as our main, since our song skills were so dependant on it. Not until the great melee patch just before luclin came out were we able to left wield our epics and still get the instrument mod. I Wielded epic in main over a 13 17 club that procced a 150ish fire based dd; if that doesn't tell you how much I value the mod the sss gives I'm not sure what will.<br>
<br>
so back to the main thread, singing mods started with the revised epic. This mod helped most singing based songs except haste/slow (incidentally the string based mana regen on 55 canata was never helped by a lute nor epic).<br>
<br>
enter in luclin and two major events happened with regards to instrument mods:<br>
AA skills<br>
Amp song effect<br>
<br>
First of these is AA skills...<br>
2 Class skills help directly our instrument base mod...<br>
instrument mastery is +.2/+.4/.+6 total which used to effect all 4 instruemnt skills always AND singing.<br>
im was nerfed recently after luclin had been out about 8 months so that it no longer helped singing based mods.<br>
at the same time, singing mastery, which only helps our singing mod was boosted from +.1/+.2/+.3 total to match im's bonus of +.2/+.4/+.6.. thanks verant , like 18 AA is a walk in the park to waste on a skill we had just had not a day prior.<br>
<br>
jam fest helps songs in a way that bypasses instrument mods and doesn't even help 32 mana period... so I'll pass by it.<br>
<br>
The other major change was amp spell. Amp boosts singing by a set percent based on level... At 60, amp helps by adding +.9 to singing based songs and lasts 30 seconds.... 5 tics max.<br>
2 known items drop amp effect clicks that last 12 mins...<br>
a crystal from ssra is +.6 and a cloak from akheva is +.9<br>
<br>
all these mods are confusing so I'll confine to singing since 32 mana is based upon that modifier.<br>
<br>
base is 1.0<br>
epic is 1.8<br>
sm = level times +.2 (if you want level two or three, plevel me when I'm at work)<br>
focus crystal = +.6<br>
focus cloak = +.9<br>
Amp = +.9 @60 (+1.0 with jamfest 3... don't ask mk?)<br>
<br>
so since my guild has better things to do than hit any mobs in akheva (I don't blame them) I'm &quot;stuck&quot; with a focus crystal which I've gotten for all the active bards in my guild. I also got sm1 because someone had to tell the other bards wtf it did.<br>
<br>
so lets count that up...<br>
<br>
1.8 + .6 + .2 = 2.6<br>
amp (or that #$%^#$^#$ cloak) would bring me to 3.6, the cap incidentally for bard mods.<br>
<br>
now the base mana that 32 regens is 7 mana ONCE per tic (if you try and spam mana 32 every 3 seconds, you get phantom mana.<br>
<br>
with just my normal gear and gem clicky up, that's 7 times 2.6 = 18.2 =&gt; 18 mana every time I twist in 32<br>
<br>
eventually(uh maybe not) I'll get the other two points of singing mastery for another +.4 but because of a round off error verant has ignore for nearly 4 years, it'll only be 20 mana.<br>
<br>
Now for me, if I twist in amp too, I net my group another 7 mana per cast..... that's 1 more than the vast majority of level 60 bards.<br>
<br>
Now in a raid situation, I have alot of other duties which this  is not the place to go into. For a caster group I play 32 mana  but since it has only a 30 foot range and no icon, and I have to be in the right place to both occ and anc aoe mana the clerics..... well more often than not the wizzys are not even within range.<br>
<br>
If amp was so important to my guild, I figure they'd at least TRY shei once for the click. It isn't though so my wasting a song slot , not to mention a twist slot on amp just aint happening. Oh and before anyone thinks I'm bitter about no shei cloak, I'm not really. To be honest that's another 4+ casters with ft 15 which I'm allll for.<br>
<br>
So a few leasons for this..<br>
1. I didn't bother meming amp for ~1 mana per second .... um ever. Damage sheilds yes.<br>
2. beware using generalizations lest someone from another board link it<br>
3. your knowing about bards got better! (3)<br>
<br>
Cheers!<br>
-Liq <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarayalebon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Araya LeBon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 391<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/15/02 8:29:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3630.topic&index=27>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hi</span><hr size=1> Who knew that bards were such a disgruntled bunch?  You guys should form a union or something...you're worse than enchies.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46329"><img src="http://www.netwalk.com/~loki/signaturevara.jpg"><BR>60 Iksar Grandmaster<a> - Shackle of Tynnonium - Celestial Fist -<BR>
